=========================================================
std::thread (C++ INTERVIEW NOTES)
=========================================================

Definition
----------

std::thread is a C++11 class used to create and manage threads.

Each std::thread object represents one thread of execution.

Header:
--------
#include <thread>

---------------------------------------------------------

Basic Syntax

std::thread t(functionName);

---------------------------------------------------------

Example

#include <iostream>
#include <thread>
using namespace std;

void print()
{
    cout << "Thread is running\n";
}

int main()
{
    thread t(print);

    t.join();

    return 0;
}

Output:

Thread is running

---------------------------------------------------------

How It Works

Main Thread

↓

Creates std::thread

↓

New thread starts executing print()

↓

Both threads execute concurrently

↓

join() waits for the thread to finish

---------------------------------------------------------

Creating Thread using Lambda

thread t([]()
{
    cout << "Hello from thread\n";
});

t.join();

---------------------------------------------------------

Creating Thread for Member Function

class Test
{
public:
    void display()
    {
        cout << "Member function\n";
    }
};

Test obj;

thread t(&Test::display, &obj);

t.join();

---------------------------------------------------------

Passing Arguments

void print(int x)
{
    cout << x << endl;
}

thread t(print, 10);

t.join();

---------------------------------------------------------

Important Member Functions

✓ join()
  Waits for thread completion.

✓ detach()
  Runs thread independently.

✓ joinable()
  Checks whether the thread can be joined or detached.

---------------------------------------------------------

Interview Points

✓ Introduced in C++11.
✓ Represents a single thread of execution.
✓ Thread starts immediately after construction.
✓ Must call join() or detach() before the thread object is destroyed.

---------------------------------------------------------

One-line Interview Answer

"std::thread is a C++11 class that creates and manages a separate thread of execution, allowing tasks to run concurrently."
